> @alcolmenar I am not sure if I understand exactly what you are calling "Debug Log", but I set the LSP log level to DEBUG and logged it. How does it look?

Looks good and thanks. It does appear that the LSP is leveraging the errant code. If we look at what's being received from the LSP:

```lua
{
	id = 2,
	jsonrpc = "2.0",
	result = {
		{
			newText = "",
			range = {
				["end"] = { character = 0, line = 3 },
				start = { character = 0, line = 0 },
			},
		},
		{
			newText = "{\n",
			range = {
				["end"] = { character = 0, line = 3 },
				start = { character = 0, line = 3 },
			},
		},
		{
			newText = '  "foo": "bar"\n',
			range = {
				["end"] = { character = 0, line = 3 },
				start = { character = 0, line = 3 },
			},
		},
		{
			newText = "}\n",
			range = {
				["end"] = { character = 0, line = 3 },
				start = { character = 0, line = 3 },
			},
		},
	},
}
```

The result field is an array of text edits. Elements 2-4 all have the same start position and with the "fix", these aren't being applied in reverse order anymore. Because they have the same start position and the same end position, the `newText` is inserted at that position without any overwrite. This results in the issue that you're seeing. Hope that makes sense
